## 1. Color Rules (Keep It Expensive)

### 1.1 Neutrals Dominate; Color is a Signal

**Rule**: Neutrals = 85-95% of UI. Primary blue = 3-10%. Gold accent = 1-3%.

**Color Distribution**:
- **Neutrals** (backgrounds, text, borders): 85-95%
- **Primary blue** (links, primary actions, key highlights): 3-10%
- **Gold accent** (tiny highlights only): 1-3%

**❌ FORBIDDEN**: If gold appears more than "a few touches per screen," it stops feeling premium.

**Brand Colors**:
```typescript
// Primary Brand Color
primary: {
  main: '#0B3C78',      // Royal Blue
  hover: '#072A55',     // Midnight Blue (hover/active)
  dark: '#1E5FA8',      // Royal Blue (brighter for dark theme)
  darkHover: '#2C76C9', // Luminous Blue (dark theme hover)
},

// Luxury Accent (use sparingly - 1-3% max)
accent: {
  light: '#C9A24D',     // Antique Gold (light theme)
  dark: '#D4AF37',      // Warm Gold (dark theme)
  background: '#F3E9D2', // Champagne Tint (light theme only)
},
```

**Design Guidance**:
- **Gold should never be dominant** — 1-3% usage max
- **Prefer thin lines, subtle shadows, and negative space**
- **Avoid gradients in light mode** — flat tones feel more premium
- **No pure black** — always navy-tinted (even in dark mode)
- **Gold works best on dark mode** — icons, focus rings, key numbers
- **Avoid glow effects** — rely on contrast and spacing instead

---

### 1.2 Never Use Pure Black or Pure White

**Rule**: Light theme uses off-white backgrounds and deep navy text. Dark theme uses near-black navy and soft ivory text.

**Light Theme** ("Polished Luxury"):
```typescript
background: {
  primary: '#F6F7F4',    // Soft Ivory (not #FFFFFF)
  secondary: '#ECEFF1',  // Cool Platinum (cards, sections)
  elevated: '#FFFFFF',    // Elevated surfaces
},
border: {
  default: '#D1D5D8',    // Brushed Steel (dividers, borders)
},
text: {
  primary: '#0F1E2D',    // Deep Navy (not #000000)
  secondary: '#4A5D73',  // Slate Blue-Gray
  tertiary: '#8A95A3',   // Cool Gray (muted/helper text)
},
interactive: {
  primary: '#0B3C78',    // Royal Blue
  primaryHover: '#072A55', // Midnight Blue
},
accent: {
  gold: '#C9A24D',       // Antique Gold (icons, highlights)
  goldBackground: '#F3E9D2', // Champagne Tint
},
```

**Dark Theme** ("Midnight Precision"):
```typescript
background: {
  primary: '#0A1420',    // Near-Black Navy (not #000000)
  secondary: '#121E2B',  // Deep Steel Blue (cards)
  elevated: '#182636',   // Charcoal Navy (modals)
},
border: {
  default: '#223447',    // Blue-Gray Steel (dividers, hairline accents)
},
text: {
  primary: '#E6E8E5',    // Soft Ivory (not #FFFFFF)
  secondary: '#A8B1BC',  // Muted Steel
  tertiary: '#6F7A85',   // Cool Gray (disabled/subtle)
},
interactive: {
  primary: '#1E5FA8',    // Royal Blue (brighter for contrast)
  primaryHover: '#2C76C9', // Luminous Blue
},
accent: {
  gold: '#D4AF37',       // Warm Gold (icons, focus rings, key numbers)
},
```

---

### 1.3 One Accent Per Component

**Rule**: A button is either Primary (blue), Neutral (surface), or Destructive (rare, controlled). Never mix blue + gold in the same control.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
<Button variant="primary" />   // Blue
<Button variant="secondary" /> // Neutral surface
<Button variant="destructive" /> // Red (rare)
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
<Button style={{
  backgroundColor: theme.interactive.primary, // Blue
  borderColor: theme.accent.gold,             // Gold - NO!
}} />
```

