## 3. Iconography and Imagery Rules

### 3.1 One Icon Library, One Style

**Rule**: Either all outline or all filled. Consistent stroke width.

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// Choose one icon set and stick to it
import { Icon } from '@expo/vector-icons/Ionicons';

// All icons use same style
<Icon name="home-outline" size={20} />      // Outline style
<Icon name="settings-outline" size={20} />  // Outline style
<Icon name="user-outline" size={20} />      // Outline style

// ❌ BAD: Mixed styles
<Icon name="home" size={20} />              // Filled
<Icon name="settings-outline" size={20} />  // Outline - inconsistent!
```

---

### 3.2 Photography is Rare and Intentional

**Rule**: Luxury UI uses fewer images. If images exist, use consistent aspect ratios and rounded corners.

**Guidelines**:
- Use images sparingly
- Consistent aspect ratios (e.g., 16:9, 1:1, 4:3)
- Rounded corners match card radius
- No mixed "stock photo + illustration" styles

---

## Quick Reference

### Color Distribution
- **Neutrals**: 85-95% (backgrounds, text, borders)
- **Primary blue**: 3-10% (links, primary actions)
- **Gold accent**: 1-3% (tiny highlights only)

### Border/Shadow Guidelines
- **Default**: Hairline borders (`StyleSheet.hairlineWidth`)
- **Shadows**: Only for modals/floating elements (subtle)
- **Gradients**: Avoid in light mode
- **Glow effects**: Never use

### Border Radius
- **Small controls**: 10-12px
- **Cards**: 14-16px
- **Sheets/Modals**: 18-24px

### Iconography
- **Style**: Pick one (all outline OR all filled)
- **Library**: Consistent icon set (e.g., Ionicons)
- **Size**: Standard sizes (16, 20, 24px)

